<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFFFFFD4FF8DFD31FC9CFC5E" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFFFFFD4FF8DFD31FC9CFC5E" blockId="37.[113,1089,727,1006]" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFFFFD4FF8DFD31FF5EFD5E" bold="true" box="[113,224,727,750]" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFFFFD4FF15FD31FE3CFD5E" author="SPAETH" box="[233,386,727,750]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">SPAETH (1911)</bibRefCitation>
established the genus 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FD81FD31FD73FD5E" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[637,717,727,750]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFFFFD4FD81FD31FD73FD5E" box="[637,717,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Orexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for conspicuous group of species described in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FE98FD11FD2FFCBE" authority="Chevrolat, 1836" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[356,657,759,782]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFFFFD4FE98FD11FE63FCBE" box="[356,477,759,782]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Coptocycla</emphasis>
Chevrolat, 1836
</taxonomicName>
, and characterized by large and flattened body. Spaeth pointed that this group of species is however more related to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FC66FCF1FBB5FC9E" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1854" box="[922,1035,791,814]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Physonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFFFFD4FC66FCF1FBB5FC9E" box="[922,1035,791,814]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Physonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to other species classified as 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FE5CFCD1FDA7FCFE" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[416,537,823,846]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFFFFD4FE5CFCD1FDA7FCFE" box="[416,537,823,846]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Coptocycla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as they differ in flat prosternum, elongate tarsomere IV and short antennae in proportion to body length. However, he kept 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FC8DFCB1FC7FFCDE" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[881,961,855,878]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFFFFD4FC8DFCB1FC7FFCDE" box="[881,961,855,878]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Orexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FF8DFC91FF6AFC3E" authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[113,212,887,910]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFFFFD4FF18FC91FED2FC3E" author="SPAETH" box="[228,364,887,910]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" refId="ref50998" refString="SPAETH F. 1914: Chrysomelidae: 16. Cassidinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 62. W. Junk, Berlin, 180 pp." type="book" year="1914">SPAETH 1914</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFFFFD4FE8BFC91FE10FC3E" author="SPAETH" box="[375,430,887,910]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" pagination="11 - 43" refId="ref51435" refString="SPAETH F. 1942: Cassidinae (Col. Chrysom.). Pp. 11 - 43. In: TITSCHACK E. (ed.): Beitrage zur Fauna Perus. Nach der Ausbeute der Hamburger Sudperu-Expedition 1936, anderer Sammlungen, wie auch auf Grund von Literaturangaben. Band II. Lief. 1. Conradt Behne, Hamburg." type="book chapter" year="1942">1942</bibRefCitation>
) and subsequent authors accepted this position (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFFFFD4FC4DFC91FB83FC3E" author="HINCKS" box="[945,1085,887,910]" firstAuthor="HINCKS" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" pagination="327 - 358" refId="ref49715" refString="HINCKS W. D. 1952: The genera of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 103: 327 - 358." type="journal article" year="1952">HINCKS 1952</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFFFFD4FF8DFC71FE98FC1E" author="BOROWIEC" box="[113,294,919,942]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC 1999a</bibRefCitation>
). I concur with 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFFFFD4FE2CFC71FDC4FC1E" author="SPAETH's" box="[464,634,919,942]" firstAuthor="SPAETH's" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" pagination="239 - 277" refId="ref50915" refString="SPAETH F. 1911: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen VIII. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 61: 239 - 277." type="journal article" year="1911">SPAETHʼs (1911)</bibRefCitation>
findings and hereby transfer 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FC49FC71FBBBFC1E" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1911" box="[949,1029,919,942]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orexita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFFFFD4FC49FC71FBBBFC1E" box="[949,1029,919,942]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="312">Orexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FF8DFC51FF6AFC7E" authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[113,212,951,974]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FF0FFC51FE10FC7E" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[243,430,951,974]" pageId="37" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FE4AFC51FDD3FC7E" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[438,621,951,974]" pageId="37" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
differ in having a transverse head with small eyes, while 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFFFFD4FF0CFC31FEEDFC5E" authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[240,339,983,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
have circular head, mostly with large eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
